</head><body><div class=3D"observablehq-root"><div class=3D"observablehq ob=
servablehq--worker" dir=3D"auto" style=3D"margin-bottom: 17px;"><h1 id=3D"o=
rigami-stripe-calculator">Origami stripe calculator</h1></div><div class=3D=
"observablehq observablehq--worker" dir=3D"auto" style=3D"margin-bottom: 17=
px;"><div><p>This is a work-in-progress tool to play around with generating=
 colour-change stripes for origami models.</p>
<p>It=E2=80=98s based on a technique taught to me by Steven Casey (and used=
 in his Numbat design), then generalised for multiple parameters. I origina=
lly started this just to calculate how much paper would be used for specifi=
c values. Then it kind of got away from me.</p>
<p>Play with the sliders to change the model=E2=80=99s parameters.</p>
<p>I might turn this into a proper dedicated web app at some point. <em>Mig=
ht.</em></p>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> I=E2=80=99m still testing out ideas, so this is l=
ikely to be buggy.</p>
<p>Some future ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Asymmetric fold angles.</li>
<li>Stripes of different lengths.</li>
<li>Export to <code>.cp</code> or <code>.fold</code> format.</li>
</ul></div></div><div class=3D"observablehq observablehq--worker" dir=3D"au=
to" style=3D"margin-bottom: 17px;"><span><p class=3D"figure-desc">Folded fi=
gure with indicative layering:</p>
